### Test User List with Activation Status
### This tests the updated user listing with activation status column

### 1. Get All Users (should show activation status)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/users
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 2. Create a User (will be inactive by default)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

### 3. Get Users Again (should show new user as "Pending")
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/users
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 4. Activate the User
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/activate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "activationCode": "ACTIVATION_CODE_FROM_EMAIL",
  "password": "password123",
  "username": "testuser"
}

### 5. Get Users Again (should show user as "Active")
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/users
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE




